  "texts": [
    "Some motivations for changing assessment were due to the facilitating conditions (n = 12), with the widespread emergence of AI tools in teaching and learning being an environmental catalyst (\"for me it is part of digital transformation of education\").",
    "Other individuals/stakeholders played some roles to motivate teachers to apply AI tools in their assessment processes (social influence, n = 10).",
    "They explicitly stated that \"there were a lot of people use it\" and \"there's nowhere to hide\" from AI tools.",
    "They agreed \"to adapt\" to the new changes in order to \"not be left behind\".",
    "A few teachers indicated hedonic motivation (n = 7) was one of the reasons they changed how to assess students (\"I'm excited about AI\")."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}